"Oh, it is childish. She dropped her bouquet as we went towards the vestry. She was passing the
front pew at the time, and it fell over into the pew. There was a moment's delay, but the gentleman
in the pew handed it up to her again, and it did not appear to be the worse for the fall. Yet when I
spoke to her of the matter, she answered me abruptly; and in the carriage, on our way home, she
seemed absurdly agitated over this trifling cause."

"Indeed! You say that there was a gentleman in the pew. Some of the general public were present,
then?"

"Oh, yes. It is impossible to exclude them when the church is open."